parameters.name: SCID
parameters.description:
Spacecraft ID
                        SCID = 'P10x' for Pioneer 10 where 'x' is an
                        identifier that specifies the processing scheme

parameters.name: YRDAY
parameters.description:
Real number containing year (19YY) and the day of
                        year (DDD) in the form (YYDDD.0).

parameters.name: NSEC
parameters.description:
Real number containing time in seconds of day
                        from 0.0 to 86400.0.

parameters.name: RAD
parameters.description: Heliocentric distance in kilometers.

parameters.name: HLONG
parameters.description: Ecliptic longitude of s/c in degrees.

parameters.name: HLAT
parameters.description: Ecliptic latitude of s/c in degrees.

parameters.name: CHISQ
parameters.description:
Formal value of chi-squared from the 
                        least-squares fit software used to calculate 
                        plasma parameters.

parameters.name: BADREC
parameters.description:
Data quality index.
  
                        ABS( BADREC) < 5.0           Good data
                        5.0 < ABS( BADREC) < 15.0    Good data
                        15.0 < ABS( BADREC) < 25.0   Less reliable data
                        25.0 < ABS( BADREC)          Bad data.

parameters.name: BSCA
parameters.description:
Space to hold average of the absolute value of the
                        interplanetary magnetic field. Currently empty!

parameters.name: BMAG
parameters.description:
Space to hold average of the magnitude of the
                        average interplanetary magnetic field. Currently 
                        empty!

parameters.name: BAZM
parameters.description:
Space to hold the azimuthal (E/W) angle of the 
                        average interplanetary magnetic field.  Zero 
                        points TOWARDS the sun (?) and positive values 
                        point towards the EAST (?). Currently empty!

parameters.name: BPOL
parameters.description:
Space to hold the polar (N/W) angle of the 
                        average interplanetary magnetic field.  Zero 
                        points TOWARDS the sun (?) and positive values 
                        point towards the NORTH (?).  Currently empty!

parameters.name: DAVGBM
parameters.description:
RMS dispersion in average of magnitude of B.
                        Space to hold the RMS dispersion in average of 
                        magnitude of B. Currently empty!

parameters.name: DBMAG
parameters.description:
Space to hold the RMS dispersion in magnitude of 
                        magnitude of B. Currently empty!

parameters.name: DBAZM
parameters.description:
Space to hold the RMS dispersion in azimuthal 
                        (E/W) angle of the average interplanetary magnetic
                        field. Currently empty!

parameters.name: DBPOL
parameters.description:
Space to hold the RMS dispersion in polar (N/S)
                        angle of the average interplanetary magnetic
                        field. Currently empty!

parameters.name: TEM
parameters.description:
Should be accurate to 20% when T > 10,000 K.
                        Should be accurate to 40% when 10,000 K > T > 
                        5,000 K. Unreliable when T < 5,000 K.
                        Solar wind proton temperature.

parameters.name: DEN
parameters.description:
Should be accurate to 20% at Pioneer 10 prior to 1992.
                        Should be accurate to 50% at Pioneer 10 after 
                        1992 (Detector A Total Flux Measurements).
                        WARNING!  These Pioneer 10 Detector A Total Flux
                        densities (SCID = 'P10E' or 'P10G') appear to be 
                        50% higher than densities from the other 
                        measurement schemes when solar wind temperatures
                        are low!
                        
                        Solar wind proton number density

parameters.name: VEL
parameters.description:
Should be accurate to 2-5 km / sec
                        approximately 200.0 to 1500.0.
                        Solar wind speed

parameters.name: AZM
parameters.description:
Azimuthal (E/W) angle of the solar wind bulk 
                        velocity in the RTN system. Zero points AWAY
                        from the sun and positive values point towards 
                        the EAST (in the direction of planetary 
                        rotation).
                        (This is going to change-temp)

parameters.name: POL
parameters.description:
Unknown, but may be approximately 3 degrees at
                        Pioneer 10 prior to 1983. Polar (N/S) angle of 
                        the solar wind bulk velocity in the RTN system. 
                        Zero points AWAY from the sun and positive 
                        values point towards the NORTH.

parameters.name: DTEM
parameters.description:
Formal value of the uncertainty in proton
                        temperature (K) calculated by the least squares
                        fit software.

parameters.name: DDEN
parameters.description:
Formal value of the uncertainty in the proton
                        density calculated by the least squares fit
                        software.

parameters.name: DVEL
parameters.description:
Formal value of the uncertainty in the solar wind
                        speed calculated by the least squares fit 
                        software.

parameters.name: DAZM
parameters.description:
Formal value of the uncertainty in the azimuthal
                        flow angle calculated by the least squares fit
                        software.

parameters.name: DPOL
parameters.description:
Formal value of the uncertainty in the polar
                        flow angle calculated by the least squares fit
                        software.

parameters.name: DPROC
parameters.description:
Real number containing processing date in the 
                        form (YYDDD.0)
